Introduction

JO1 is an eleven-member Japanese boy group under LAPONE Entertainment. They were formed from the winners of Produce 101 Japan. The Members include Sho, Ren, Ruki, Junki, Keigo, Takumi, Syoya, Shosei, Sukai, Shion and Mamehara Issei. They debuted on March 4th, 2020, with their single Protostar

The "J" in JO1 refers to Japan, the group's origin, while the "01" stands for the first year of the Reiwa period in which the group was formed. The fans of JO1 are known as "JAM", which stands for "JO1 and Me", representing the bond between JO1 and their fans.

Besides Japan, the group promoted their music in South Korea and appeared on several music shows.
